challenges.desc: Merry #Christmas!
challenges.title: christmas

contents.desc: 10 tips for those of you who are planning their trip to London this Christmas 🎄
♥️ If you come in November most xmas lights will be on and it’s cheaper and less crowded
✨ Go on a light trail at Kew Gardens or Syon Park (book well in advance)
⛄️ Covent Garden is sprinkled with snow every hour on the hour starting at 12pm, plan your visit around that
🎶 Book ‘Carols at the Hall’ at the Royal Albert Hall
☕️ Book an afternoon tea bus to see the decorations while enjoying tea
💥 Each area has a big party to switch their lights on. Follow this account as we will be posting the dates
🚂 Go on a day trip to Blenheim Palace to see the magic light trail (1h from London)
🫖 Go for a festive afternoon tea (Savoy, Claridge’s, the Ritz and Lanesborough are our fav)
🎅🏻 Go to the most festive bar in London Miracle at Henrietta
🍻 Go to the most festive pub in town The Churchill Arms Notting Hill

stickerText: 10 tips if you are planning your trip to London this Christmas
If you come in November most xmas lights will be on and it’s cheaper and less crowded
Go on a light trail at Kew Gardens or Syon Park (book well in advance)
Covent Garden is sprinkled with snow every hour on the hour starting at 12pm, plan your visit around that
Book an afternoon tea bus to see the decorations while enjoying tea and cakes
Go to the most festive pub in town The Churchill Arms Notting Hill
Book ‘Carols at the Hall’ at the Royal Albert Hall
Each area has a big party to switch their lights on. Follow this account as we will be posting the dates
Go on a day trip to Blenheim Palace to see the magic light trail (1h from London)
Go for a festive afternoon tea (Savoy, Claridge’s, the Ritz and Lanesborough are our favourite ones)
Go to the most festive bar in London ‘Miracle at Henrietta’
